<br>
The problem as it is currently is almost every cleric is already at the end.  So if you move the bottleneck you're still going to have 50 clerics doing their turn in.<br>
<br>
I also wonder if we're not at the point where the bottlenecks just don't server a purpose anymore.  I'm not saying they should throw the servers wide open, but they do need to open the floodgates a little more.  I think if it's pre-vellious it shouldn't be on a 7 day timer.  CT and Inny were retuned after Vellious right?  I'd like to see everything that was on a 7 day timer go to a 2-3 day timer.<br>
<br>
One of the biggest problems with the bottlenecks is they're designed for a certiain % of the population.  However the server has a MUCH MUCH higerh % of the population in that level range now.  That's been the biggest pain in the buttocks that Verant hasn't figured out yet.<br>
<br>
If 50% of the pop. are warriors, 35% are rangers and 5% are Bards, then Cobalt should drop almost twice as much as Tolans' and a hell of a lot more than Singing Steel just for an example.  I think everyone can remember the 10K Cobalt Boots vs the 500pp SS boots you freakin couldn't give away.  As soon as VI figures out how to balance their game for the class population disparities I think they've solved their last big problem. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/uelkanah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elkanah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cons Threateningly </span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#333333>(7/24/02 6:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/fguild75784frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=150.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rage aftermath</span><hr size=1> Heimdall, you're now treading on class balance issues.<br>
