<br>
Rating 1 - 10. 10 being most dificult, 1 being easiest.<br>
<br>
Rogue - 1<br>
Monk - 2<br>
Druid - 3<br>
Shaman - 3 <br>
Ranger - 4<br>
Paladin - 5<br>
Enchanter - 6 <br>
Wizard - 7<br>
Cleric - 7<br>
Necromancer - 8<br>
Shadowknight - 9 <br>
Warrior - 9<br>
Magician - 10<br>
Beastlord - Who cares? <br>
<br>
Several factors play into this. Usefullness, for one. You don't exactly see alot of guilds killing themselves to get Wizards their epic, where you do see more willingness to participate in said encounters with... oh let's say, Cleric epic. A fair assessment, no?<br>
<br>
Then we take actually having to have a guild capable of raiding an alternate plane of exsistance into it. I.e. A rogue only has to sneak/hide in Hate to get their piece from there, correct? Monks only have to clear the 1st island in Sky (And c'mon, thats easy as all hell). Druids don't even have to go to another plane for theirs. Etc etc...<br>
<br>
Then we look at who has to kill what mobs. For example: Killing the general for the Rogue epic isn't nearly as hard as having to fight all the way to the 7th isle in Sky (hihi mages~).<br>
<br>
Then we look at how contested the spawns are. The only reason Cleric is listed at a 7, for example, is our old friend Ragefire. Where Shaman, for example, don't have it so hard.<br>
<br>
Then take into consideration how often a mob drops whatever piece is needed. Warriors have a hell of a time with the scales they need to get (and Paladins with books) as opposed to say... Druids and VSR.<br>
<br>
I think overall, while we may disagree on the actual numbers here, I got it pretty close to accurate on the actual list. /shrug I'm bored. =)<br>
